article.headline: George Mason 73, James Madison 52
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- John Vaughan's 16 points led four players in double figures as George Mason defeated James Madison 73-52 on Saturday. George Mason (9-7, 3-3 Colonial Athletic Association) turned a sizable 39-23 half time advantage into a rout with a 34-12 burst to start the second half. The Patriots' largest lead was 71-39 and came on a 3-pointer by Vaughan, his fourth of the game. Juwann James scored 21 points to lead James Madison (4-12, 1-5). The victory was the third straight for George Mason, which opened conference play with three consecutive losses. Will Thomas had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Patriots. Also hitting double figures for George Mason were Dre Smith (11) and Jordan Carter (11). The Patriots hit a season high 11 3-pointers and were 11 of 24 from behind the arc. George Mason shot 50 percent (29 of 58) from the floor. Led by Smith, who connected on two 3-pointers during a 15-4 Patriots run, George Mason erased an early first half deficit and took control with a 24-14 lead. James Madison cut the deficit to 24-19 with 6:05 remaining in the half on a basket by James before the Patriots stymied the Dukes' rally. The Patriots' Chris Fleming suffered a sprained right ankle early in the first half and did not play in the second half. George Mason has won the last five meetings against James Madison.
